(249, 1, '2014-08-12 06:52:33', '2014-08-12 06:52:33', '<p class="p1"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">It’s obvious that generating revenue through sales is what keeps a business running. With a subscription based business, capturing early product sales and managing risks to retain those customers have an important role in generating futures sales.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>How can you accelerate early sales and retain customers? </b></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">It starts with introducing your solution in an appropriate way and engaging trusted, local influencers to build credibility.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">We have a framework of <b>5 Customer Funnels</b> you can use to follow the customer through their product journey and ideas on how you can bring them along each step of the way (Figure 1).</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>5 Customer Funnels</b></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1"><b>Acquisition</b> – People come to your site after they’ve heard about you through email, press, blogs, word of mouth, and other paid or unpaid channels.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1"><b>Activation</b> – If people like what they see on the landing page, email invitation, app store or other form of advertising they’ll become users by creating an account and beginning   their free trial.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1"><b>Retention</b> – Users come back to the app through unsolicited use, emails reminders or push notifications and stay active through features they encounter while using the product.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1"><b>Revenue</b> – You monetize active users through paid subscriptions.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1"><b>Referral</b> – Active users refer others through viral product features and other incentives.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Figure 1</b></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Let’s take a deeper dive into each of these.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Acquisition &amp; Activation</b></p>\r\n<p class="p1">This is all about getting customers interested in what you have to offer (acquisition) and getting them to begin the trial (activation). Prior to actually acquiring customers, you’ll want to answer some questions to help refine messaging for the product.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">To begin, let’s define the value proposition – the primary reason a customer should buy from you.  Once defined, this is first thing visitors should see on the landing page and all major entry points.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Answers (from people who could become real customers) on a few basic questions can help to determine the language of your customer and further define your value proposition.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">How can I save or acquire more time/money/information using this product?</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">How can improve my perceived worth/quality in front of my clients/peers?</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">How can I feel personally rewarded?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Examples of product features/benefits and opportunities from these 3 questions include the following:</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">How can I save or acquire more time/money/information using this product?</span></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Pre-choreographed music and workouts saves you time.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Less expensive than DVD’s</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Access content only available here</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Teach classes anywhere</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">How can improve my perceived worth/quality in front of my clients/peers?</span></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Content updated regularly to keep classes fresh</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">How can I feel personally rewarded?</span></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Early access to events</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Exclusive offers/promotions</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">On your product landing page then, the value proposition is usually a block of text (a headline, sub-headline and one paragraph of text) with a visual (photo, hero shot, graphics).</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">There is no one right way to go about it, but I suggest you start with the following formula:</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Headline. What is the end-benefit you’re offering, in 1 short sentence.  An attention grabber.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Sub-headline or a 2-3 sentence paragraph. A specific explanation of what you do/offer, for whom and why is it useful.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">3 bullet points. List the key benefits or features.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Visual. Images communicate much faster than words. Show the product, the hero shot or an image reinforcing your main message.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Solve their objections</span></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Next, make it easy for them to begin. Supporting value add-copy can help reduce reasons a customer may not purchase or begin a trial.  Examples include:</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Free trial</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Monthly to Month agreement, cancel any time</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Money-back guarantee</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Limited time discount</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Demonstrating the actual, tangible solution is often the best way to introduce something new. Every new solution can benefit from a well-designed demonstration. The free trial along with a video tutorial or other interactive content helps show which aspects of your solution pose the biggest perceived risk to your customer.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">On top of this, other marketing activities to consider include the following:</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Landing page optimization\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Making the product simple to purchase and easy to try before they buy.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Creating a remarkable customer experience through design and content.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Creating a separate product landing page to accurately track and manage.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Site A/B Testing to optimize copy and design.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Email\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Testing email campaigns to optimize conversion</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Evaluating open, click thru and conversion rates</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Auto-responder if cart abandonment</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Automate remarketing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">SEO\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Capture interested potential customers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Content Marketing\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Leveraging blog posts, infographics, and videos to increase awareness and site traffic</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Paid Acquisition\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Search engine marketing (Google AdWords; Facebook ads; display ads; mobile ads).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Next, establish credibility by aligning customer influencers. Who do your customers listen to in the your industry?</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Get their early buy-in, familiarization with the product and recognize them for their importance to the company.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Selective extended trials (a full year) exchange for testimonials. Capture written and video testimonials about the benefits of the program</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n	<li class="li1">Social Media\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Have a coordinated/scripted social medial messaging and cadence developed for their use.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Retention:</b></p>\r\n<p class="p1">The number one goal is to have customer retention. Successfully solving a customer’s problem and continuing to engage them enables a long-standing relationship to develop.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Engagement is built into the product, as this is a critical component to long-term program success.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Some goals with retention are to maintain the buzz and excitement of the product and deepen the connection with the community of subscribers.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Live conversations\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Speaking with a small number of active customers and those who cancelled.  Provides great feedback about what is working well and more importantly what needs to be improved.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Surveys\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Use tools including Survey Monkey and Net Promoter Score (a good leading indicator of other metrics) to measure their willingness to refer the product and affinity for existing or proposed features.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Email/Push</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Auto-responder emails are built into our platform based on user interaction with the app.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Push notifications with content updates and encourage social sharing</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Exclusive member newsletter or email communication and promotions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Revenue</b>:</p>\r\n<p class="p1">With a simple monthly subscription and reasonable rates there’s not much do here.  If you are having issues with retention it’s either a product or pricing problem.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Communicating with customers is a sure way to find our what they want from the product.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Referral:</b></p>\r\n<p class="p1">With any great solution, this will happen naturally, but probably not as quickly as you would like. It is important to look for points where you can influence the natural process to accelerate widespread adoption and to provide easy ways for people to talk and share about the program.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Building buzz: recommendations &amp; referrals</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Encourage users to share through social media</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Sales reps and industry partners</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Where to begin</b></p>\r\n<p class="p1">It’s impossible to focus your efforts on each of these steps at the same time.  Choose one of the five funnels and focus relentlessly on improving, then reassess and begin again. We recommend a 5 Step process for considerations when planning your efforts.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">Prioritize the plan. What are the 1 or 2 metrics we want to improve?</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">List our intent. Why do we want to change?</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">List the customer friction to solve. What’s the user experience problem?</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Determine baseline conversion. What is the current status?</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Consider potential lift from test. How much do we expect to gain?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">As an example, let’s assume we are in the acquisition phase and we’ve already emailed an invitation to begin the free trial to a portion of the potential customer list.  We’ve noticed the open rates of the email are lower than expected.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Going through the 5 Steps is as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">We want to improve email open rates</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">To increase the number of people who have the opportunity to begin a free trial</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">They aren’t finding the subject line compelling enough to open</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Current open rates are 20%</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Expect a 10% lift with a change to the subject line</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Or, another example would be this:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ul1">\r\n	<li class="li1">We want to improve the number of site visits to the app landing page from people not on our mailing list.</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">To increase the number of people who have the opportunity to experience our brand and begin a free trial</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">People outside of our permission marketing channels aren’t aware of what the app</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Current organic site visits account for 5% of traffic</li>\r\n	<li class="li1">Request our current users to rate the app in the app store will improve the app ranking and increase organic site visits to 7.5% within 45 days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">While having a great product is the most important success factor, a methodical and persistent approach to optimizing the customer funnels will further accelerate sales.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>', 'Simple Framework to Accelerate Revenue', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '248-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-12 06:52:33', '2014-08-12 06:52:33', '', 248, 'http://localhost/248-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(251, 1, '2014-08-12 06:53:26', '2014-08-12 06:53:26', '<p class="p1"></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">The transition from DVD’s to a subscription based video-on-demand service is here.  With the near ubiquity of Internet availability, video-on-demand allows your content to be streamed and viewed anytime.  The growth of services including Netflix, Hulu and Amazon reinforce the change in customer behaviors towards streaming content.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">While your customers appreciate the easy access to video content through streaming, why else should you put your existing DVD content in a mobile app?</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Eliminate printing and shipping costs</b></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Think about the costs to print, warehouse and ship DVD’s.  Now take all the money and invest into a mobile solution. The more DVD’s you produce and sell the more you’ll save by going digital. Still want DVD’s? Consider charging a higher price for the DVD as an incentive to for customers to move to a digital solution. Not only will you get a greater margin if they buy the DVD, you’ll also add to your Monthly Recurring Revenue (MRR) if they buy a subscription.  MRR is a key success metric in subscription based businesses.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Eliminate Piracy</b></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Illegal copies of DVD’s cost companies millions of dollars per year in both lost sales and the legal cost of battling counterfeit problems. You won’t have this problem with streaming video. While our platform allows a mobile app to be installed on more than one device, the content can only be played on one device at a time, making sharing of content unlikely.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Update your content easily</b></p>\r\n<p class="p1">The Classcast platform includes a Content Management tool so you can update your content anytime you want. New videos, new languages, whatever you want.  You have the ability to change any content, anytime.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Distribute globally at the push of a button</b></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Just added some new content or updated existing content? Once uploaded and saved the new content is available the next time the app is opened.  The ease with which you can edit your content allows you to shorten the time in product development or product updates as you get real-time feedback about what people are viewing.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">VHS and Betamax became nearly obsolete in the early 2000’s and DVD sales have been decreasing year-over-year.  While there will likely be some demand for DVD’s in the future, streaming will be leading the way. As more customers expect to view content on their mobile device, the future of streaming begins now.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>', 'Why switching from DVD’s to a subscription service is good for your business', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '250-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-12 06:53:26', '2014-08-12 06:53:26', '', 250, 'http://localhost/250-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(253, 1, '2014-08-12 06:53:47', '2014-08-12 06:53:47', '<p class="p1"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">An influencer can be thought of as someone who can shape the behaviors and purchasing decisions of others. Industries including fitness and allied health are strong relationship businesses and as such are well suited for influencer marketing. In the case of Influence Marketing the goal is to build a mutually beneficial relationship for the business, the influencer and the customer.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">In the 1970’s there was what is now a famous slogan by the banking firm E.F. Hutton: “When E.F. Hutton talks, people listen”. This is what influencers do, when they talk, people listen.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">You can think about categorizing Influencers into a four categories based on reach and relevance</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Reach</b>: how many target customers listen to the influencer</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Relevance</b>: how close are the interests between what the influencer is saying and those of the target customer.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n\r\n<table class="t1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="td1" valign="middle">\r\n<p class="p3">Low Relevance High Reach</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class="td1" valign="middle">\r\n<p class="p3">High Relevance High Reach</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="td1" valign="middle">\r\n<p class="p3">Low Relevance Low Reach</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class="td1" valign="middle">\r\n<p class="p3">High Relevance Low Reach</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Let’s imagine that you have a mobile app that’s targeted only Fitness Professional who are qualified to teach your courses. In order to access the content on the mobile app they need to have attended on of your courses and have been invited to join the app.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">For a more targeted niche product like this Relevance will be more important than reach.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Who might be influencers in each of these categories for this product?</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Low Relevance High Reach: Johhny Manziel (pro football quarterback)</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Low Relevance Low Reach:  Friend of Fitness Professional</p>\r\n<p class="p1">High Relevance High Reach: Fitness Industry presenter or companies CEO</p>\r\n<p class="p1">High Relevance Low Reach: Course Master Trainer</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Now, imagine a Yoga app that is available for anyone to access. Since the app is less targeted than the prior example, Reach will play a more important role, although Relevance still trumps Reach.</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Who might be example influencers in each of these categories for this product?</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Low Relevance High Reach: Justin Bieber</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Low Relevance Low Reach:  Companies accounts payable manager</p>\r\n<p class="p1">High Relevance High Reach: Top Yoga Bloggers</p>\r\n<p class="p1">High Relevance Low Reach: Master Trainers</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Influencer marketing involves building and sustaining relationships with the E.F. Hutton’s of your industry. To assist in evaluating your industry influencers you might consider ranking them based on their Klout Score: www.Klout.com</p>\r\n<p class="p2"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">The focus on relationships reinforces the focus isn’t about a sale or transaction to the influencer, rather for them to develop and authentic belief in what you offer. Searching for the mutually beneficial opportunities to partner with Influencers and playing the long-game strategy will enable these efforts to return their value multiple times.</p>', 'Influencer Marketing for Sustained Growth', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '252-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-12 06:53:47', '2014-08-12 06:53:47', '', 252, 'http://localhost/252-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(254, 1, '2014-08-12 07:23:05', '2014-08-12 07:23:05', 'An influencer can be thought of as someone who can shape the behaviors and purchasing decisions of others. Industries including fitness and allied health are strong relationship businesses and as such are well suited for influencer marketing. In the case of Influence Marketing the goal is to build a mutually beneficial relationship for the business, the influencer and the customer.\n&nbsp;\nIn the 1970’s there was what is now a famous slogan by the banking firm E.F. Hutton: “When E.F. Hutton talks, people listen”. This is what influencers do, when they talk, people listen.\n&nbsp;\nYou can think about categorizing Influencers into a four categories based on reach and relevance\n&nbsp;\n<strong>Reach:</strong> how many target customers listen to the influencer\n<strong>Relevance:</strong> how close are the interests between what the influencer is saying and those of the target customer.\n<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign="middle">Low Relevance High Reach</td>\n<td valign="middle">High Relevance High Reach</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="middle">Low Relevance Low Reach</td>\n<td valign="middle">High Relevance Low Reach</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\nLet’s imagine that you have a mobile app that’s targeted only Fitness Professional who are qualified to teach your courses. In order to access the content on the mobile app they need to have attended on of your courses and have been invited to join the app.\n&nbsp;\nFor a more targeted niche product like this Relevance will be more important than reach.\n&nbsp;\nWho might be influencers in each of these categories for this product?\n<blockquote>Low Relevance High Reach: Johhny Manziel (pro football quarterback)\n\nLow Relevance Low Reach:  Friend of Fitness Professional\n\nHigh Relevance High Reach: Fitness Industry presenter or companies CEO\n\nHigh Relevance Low Reach: Course Master Trainer</blockquote>\n&nbsp;\nNow, imagine a Yoga app that is available for anyone to access. Since the app is less targeted than the prior example, Reach will play a more important role, although Relevance still trumps Reach.\n&nbsp;\nWho might be example influencers in each of these categories for this product?\n&nbsp;\n<blockquote>Low Relevance High Reach: Justin Bieber\n\nLow Relevance Low Reach:  Companies accounts payable manager\n\nHigh Relevance High Reach: Top Yoga Bloggers\n\nHigh Relevance Low Reach: Master Trainers</blockquote>\n$nbsp;\nInfluencer marketing involves building and sustaining relationships with the E.F. Hutton’s of your industry. To assist in evaluating your industry influencers you might consider ranking them based on their Klout Score: <a href="www.Klout.com">www.Klout.com</a>\n$nbsp;\nThe focus on relationships reinforces the focus isn’t about a sale or transaction to the influencer, rather for them to develop and authentic belief in what you offer. Searching for the mutually beneficial opportunities to partner with Influencers and playing the long-game strategy will enable these efforts to return their value multiple times.', 'Influencer Marketing for Sustained Growth', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '252-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-08-12 07:23:05', '2014-08-12 07:23:05', '', 252, 'http://localhost/252-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(255, 1, '2014-08-12 07:01:21', '2014-08-12 07:01:21', '<p class="p1">An influencer can be thought of as someone who can shape the behaviors and purchasing decisions of others. Industries including fitness and allied health are strong relationship businesses and as such are well suited for influencer marketing. In the case of Influence Marketing the goal is to build a mutually beneficial relationship for the business, the influencer and the customer.</p>\r\n<p class="p1"></p>\r\n<p class="p1">In the 1970’s there was what is now a famous slogan by the banking firm E.F. Hutton: “When E.F. Hutton talks, people listen”. This is what influencers do, when they talk, people listen.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">You can think about categorizing Influencers into a four categories based on reach and relevance</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Reach</b>: how many target customers listen to the influencer</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><b>Relevance</b>: how close are the interests between what the influencer is saying and those of the target customer.</p>\r\n\r\n<table class="t1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="td1" valign="middle">\r\n<p class="p3">Low Relevance High Reach</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class="td1" valign="middle">\r\n<p class="p3">High Relevance High Reach</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="td1" valign="middle">\r\n<p class="p3">Low Relevance Low Reach</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class="td1" valign="middle">\r\n<p class="p3">High Relevance Low Reach</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class="p1">Let’s imagine that you have a mobile app that’s targeted only Fitness Professional who are qualified to teach your courses. In order to access the content on the mobile app they need to have attended on of your courses and have been invited to join the app.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">For a more targeted niche product like this Relevance will be more important than reach.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Who might be influencers in each of these categories for this product?</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Low Relevance High Reach: Johhny Manziel (pro football quarterback)</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Low Relevance Low Reach:  Friend of Fitness Professional</p>\r\n<p class="p1">High Relevance High Reach: Fitness Industry presenter or companies CEO</p>\r\n<p class="p1">High Relevance Low Reach: Course Master Trainer</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Now, imagine a Yoga app that is available for anyone to access. Since the app is less targeted than the prior example, Reach will play a more important role, although Relevance still trumps Reach.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Who might be example influencers in each of these categories for this product?</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Low Relevance High Reach: Justin Bieber</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Low Relevance Low Reach:  Companies accounts payable manager</p>\r\n<p class="p1">High Relevance High Reach: Top Yoga Bloggers</p>\r\n<p class="p1">High Relevance Low Reach: Master Trainers</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Influencer marketing involves building and sustaining relationships with the E.F. Hutton’s of your industry. To assist in evaluating your industry influencers you might consider ranking them based on their Klout Score: www.Klout.com</p>\r\n<p class="p1">The focus on relationships reinforces the focus isn’t about a sale or transaction to the influencer, rather for them to develop and authentic belief in what you offer. Searching for the mutually beneficial opportunities to partner with Influencers and playing the long-game strategy will enable these efforts to return their value multiple times.</p>', 'Influencer Marketing for Sustained Growth', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '252-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-12 07:01:21', '2014-08-12 07:01:21', '', 252, 'http://localhost/252-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
