: Course Master Trainer</blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\nNow, imagine a Yoga app that is available for anyone to access. Since the app is less targeted than the prior example, Reach will play a more important role, although Relevance still trumps Reach.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nWho might be example influencers in each of these categories for this product?\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Low Relevance High Reach: Justin Bieber\r\n\r\nLow Relevance Low Reach:  Companies accounts payable manager\r\n\r\nHigh Relevance High Reach: Top Yoga Bloggers\r\n\r\nHigh Relevance Low Reach: Master Trainers</blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\nInfluencer marketing involves building and sustaining relationships with the E.F. Hutton’s of your industry. To assist in evaluating your industry influencers you might consider ranking them based on their Klout Score: www.Klout.com\r\n&nbsp;\r\nThe focus on relationships reinforces the focus isn’t about a sale or transaction to the influencer, rather for them to develop and authentic belief in what you offer. Searching for the mutually beneficial opportunities to partner with Influencers and playing the long-game strategy will enable these efforts to return their value multiple times.', 'Influencer Marketing for Sustained Growth', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '252-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-12 07:10:27', '2014-08-12 07:10:27', '', 252, 'http://localhost/252-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
