(358, 3, '2014-09-05 06:49:18', '2014-09-05 06:49:18', '<p style="color: #4b5c66;">SAN FRANCISCO, August 15, 2014 -- Classcast was as an official sponsor of the WAFIC fitness conference in Western Australia, Australia. This sponsorship was the first in the relationship with the WAFIC conference, and Fitness Network. W</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"></p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"> and the official streaming music sponsor at Live Nation''s 2013 country music festivals. The festival partnership kicked off last weekend with Faster Horses and will continue with Watershed later this summer.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">As part of Classcast''s advertising program, they will be powering Ultimate Charts on LiveNation.com. Rdio''s sponsorship also includes advertising to music fans at Live Nation venues across the country.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">"The relationship with have with Fitness Network is  a natural fit for Classcast," says Stuart Guest-Smith, CEO of Classcast. "We''re excited to work with the best in live entertainment as it gives us a chance to engage music fans before, during and after the show."</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"><strong>About WAFIC </strong></p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">West Australian Fitness Industry Convention (WAFIC) is the world''s leading live entertainment company comprised of four market leaders: Ticketmaster.com, Live Nation Concerts, Artist Nation Management and Live Nation Media/Sponsorship. For additional information, visit www.livenation.com/investors.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">15 - 17th August, 2014</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Follow us @twitter.com/LiveNationInc</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"><strong>About ClasscastC</strong></p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Calsscast is the groundbreaking digital music service that is reinventing the way people discover, listen to, and share music. With on-demand access to over 20 million songs, Rdio connects people with music and makes it easy to search for and instantly play any song, album, artist, or playlist without ever hearing a single ad. Discover what friends, people with similar tastes, recording artists, and more are listening to in real-time and share across Twitter and Facebook. Build a digital music collection that''s available everywhere -- on the web, in-home or in-car, on tablets or mobile phones, and even offline.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Launched in August 2010, Rdio is headquartered in San Francisco and was founded by Janus Friis, the co-creator of Skype. Currently available in 31 countries, Rdio is funded by Janus Friis through his investment entities, Atomico, and Skype. For more information and to sign up, visit www.rdio.com.</p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Classcast is an Official Sponsor of the WAFIC conference in Australia ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '354-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-05 06:49:18', '2014-09-05 06:49:18', '', 354, 'http://www.classcast.co/354-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(359, 3, '2014-09-05 06:49:24', '2014-09-05 06:49:24', '<p style="color: #4b5c66;">SAN FRANCISCO, August 15, 2014 -- Classcast was as an official sponsor of the WAFIC fitness conference in Western Australia, Australia. This sponsorship was the first in the relationship with the WAFIC conference, and Fitness Network. W</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"> and the official streaming music sponsor at Live Nation''s 2013 country music festivals. The festival partnership kicked off last weekend with Faster Horses and will continue with Watershed later this summer.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">As part of Classcast''s advertising program, they will be powering Ultimate Charts on LiveNation.com. Rdio''s sponsorship also includes advertising to music fans at Live Nation venues across the country.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">"The relationship with have with Fitness Network is  a natural fit for Classcast," says Stuart Guest-Smith, CEO of Classcast. "We''re excited to work with the best in live entertainment as it gives us a chance to engage music fans before, during and after the show."</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"><strong>About WAFIC </strong></p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">West Australian Fitness Industry Convention (WAFIC) is the world''s leading live entertainment company comprised of four market leaders: Ticketmaster.com, Live Nation Concerts, Artist Nation Management and Live Nation Media/Sponsorship. For additional information, visit www.livenation.com/investors.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">15 - 17th August, 2014</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Follow us @twitter.com/LiveNationInc</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"><strong>About ClasscastC</strong></p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Calsscast is the groundbreaking digital music service that is reinventing the way people discover, listen to, and share music. With on-demand access to over 20 million songs, Rdio connects people with music and makes it easy to search for and instantly play any song, album, artist, or playlist without ever hearing a single ad. Discover what friends, people with similar tastes, recording artists, and more are listening to in real-time and share across Twitter and Facebook. Build a digital music collection that''s available everywhere -- on the web, in-home or in-car, on tablets or mobile phones, and even offline.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Launched in August 2010, Rdio is headquartered in San Francisco and was founded by Janus Friis, the co-creator of Skype. Currently available in 31 countries, Rdio is funded by Janus Friis through his investment entities, Atomico, and Skype. For more information and to sign up, visit www.rdio.com.</p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Classcast is an Official Sponsor of the WAFIC conference in Australia ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '354-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-05 06:49:24', '2014-09-05 06:49:24', '', 354, 'http://www.classcast.co/354-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(360, 1, '2014-09-07 09:08:22', '2014-09-07 09:08:22', '<p style="color: #4b5c66;"><strong>SYDNEY, 1 September 2014</strong> – Premier health, fitness and wellness provider Classcast (www.classcast.co), founded by two passionate fitness technology advocates, has today announced the availability of a completely redesigned service, providing a faster, simpler and more effective content publishing experience.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">In conjunction, the company released their new website and brand. "At Classcast we continue to improve the relationship with our customers. Our brand is an integral part of this communication and the website is key in establishing this message.  We''re excited to see this phase, and look forward to showing the industry more in the future," says Stuart Guest-Smith, CEO of Classcast.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">This is the next step in the companies journey Aidan Green, Head of Product Design at Classcast, stated it is imperative to ensure that we provide the best tools and services for our customers; and design is something at the heart of Classcast''s culture.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">“With the new Classcast, we’ve gone even further, making it simpler, faster and more visually effective to create an experience that''s unique to our industry," said Green. "We decided to specialize on the health, fitness and wellness industry, for that reason our product is built to support the range of amazing content creators out there."</p>\r\n<strong>About Classcast</strong>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Classcast is the groundbreaking content publishing platform for the health, wellness and fitness industry that is reinventing the way people discover, deliver and create content. Start earning monthly recurring revenue for your content, connect directly to your customers, and deliver content anywhere anytime - to any mobile.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">For businesses all over the world - fitness professionals, therapists, educators, life coaches, rehab specialists, physiotherapists... and many more in our amazing industry!</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Launched in October 2014, Classcast is headquartered in San Francisco and was founded by Stuart Guest-Smith and Suren Reddy. Join 1000'' of happy and growing customers today! For more information and to sign up, visit <a title="Classcast Website" href="http://www.classcast.oc">www.classcast.co.</a></p>\r\n <span style="color: #4b5c66;">Follow us @twitter.com/classcastapp</span>', 'Classcast Introduces Fresh Coat of Paint with Revamped Design', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'revamped-design', '', '', '2014-09-07 09:24:41', '2014-09-07 09:24:41', '', 0, 'http://www.classcast.co/?post_type=press&#038;p=360', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(361, 3, '2014-09-05 06:59:05', '2014-09-05 06:59:05', '<p style="color: #4b5c66;">SYDNEY, 1 September 2014 – Premier digital music service Rdio (www.rdio.com), founded by the creators of Skype, has today announced the availability of a completely redesigned service, providing a faster, simpler and more social music experience.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Unveiled at SXSW in Austin, Texas today, Rdio showcased the new Web and desktop apps and also announced that more than 15 million songs are now available in its global catalogue, marking another major milestone.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">From today, subscribers in Australia and New Zealand can experience the new Rdio, which amplifies the music discovery experience that has made the service a favourite amongst influencers, media and music fans around the world.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Despite launching in Australia and New Zealand in January, Malthe Sigurdsson, VP of Product at Rdio, stated it is imperative to stay ahead of the curve when it comes to design.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">“With the new Rdio, we’ve gone even further, making it simpler, faster and more visually appealing to create an experience that''s all about music and people,” said Sigurdsson.</p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Classcast Used Fresh Coat of Paint with Revamped Design', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '360-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-05 06:59:05', '2014-09-05 06:59:05', '', 360, 'http://www.classcast.co/360-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(362, 3, '2014-09-05 23:35:17', '2014-09-05 23:35:17', '<p style="color: #4b5c66;">SAN FRANCISCO, August 15, 2014 -- Classcast was as an official sponsor of the WAFIC fitness conference in Western Australia, Australia. This sponsorship was the first in the new relationship with the WAFIC event; and Fitness Network.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"> and the official streaming music sponsor at Live Nation''s 2013 country music festivals. The festival partnership kicked off last weekend with Faster Horses and will continue with Watershed later this summer.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">As part of Classcast''s advertising program, they will be powering Ultimate Charts on LiveNation.com. Rdio''s sponsorship also includes advertising to music fans at Live Nation venues across the country.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">"The relationship with have with Fitness Network, and WAFIC is a natural fit for Classcast," says Stuart Guest-Smith, CEO of Classcast. "We''re excited to work with the fantastic people at Fitness Network and will continue to</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"></p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">live entertainment as it gives us a chance to engage music fans before, during and after the show."</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"><strong>About WAFIC </strong></p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">West Australian Fitness Industry Convention (WAFIC) is the world''s leading live entertainment company comprised of four market leaders: Ticketmaster.com, Live Nation Concerts, Artist Nation Management and Live Nation Media/Sponsorship. For additional information, visit www.livenation.com/investors.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">15 - 17th August, 2014</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Follow us @twitter.com/ozfitnetwork</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;"><strong>About ClasscastC</strong></p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Classcast is the groundbreaking content publishing platform for the health, wellness and fitness industry that is reinventing the way people discover, listen to, and share music. With on-demand access to over 20 million songs, Rdio connects people with music and makes it easy to search for and instantly play any song, album, artist, or playlist without ever hearing a single ad. Discover what friends, people with similar tastes, recording artists, and more are listening to in real-time and share across Twitter and Facebook. Build a digital music collection that''s available everywhere -- on the web, in-home or in-car, on tablets or mobile phones, and even offline.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #4b5c66;">Launched in October 2014, Classcast is headquartered in San Francisco and was founded by Stuart Guest-Smith and Suren Reddy. Currently available in 30 countries, and translated in a range of languages.  or more information and to sign up, visit www.classcast.co.</p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Classcast is an Official Sponsor of the WAFIC conference in Australia ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '354-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-05 23:35:17', '2014-09-05 23:35:17', '', 354, 'http://www.classcast.co/354-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
