agers, support team training, executive/team briefing and more.\r\n\r\n<strong>Customer Pre-Launch</strong>\r\n\r\nReach out the early adopters to let them know what’s coming and that you’d like their support in providing feedback. Consider scheduling a series of video-conferences to provide them the opportunity to learn more details about the product and how they can help.\r\n<h2><strong>Launch and Beyond Communication</strong></h2>\r\n<strong>Internal Launch</strong>\r\n\r\nA lot of work has been completed up this point and its time to keep the traction going. Celebrate your launch and provide regular updates to the team about customer service issues, product feedback, number of trials and other conversion details.\r\n\r\n<strong>Customer Launch</strong>\r\n\r\nWhile your print ads, postcards and other will drive awareness and trial conversions, your efforts to build a two way communication with your early customers and providing them an incentive to accept your will build trust and strengthen your brand. Provide your evangelists/early adopters with suggested messaging to promote through their social channels - remember, these people want to help), design product promotion email to be sent to your customers inviting them to the two weeks free trial - their incentive to try before they buy. Begin capturing testimonials that can be used throughout your messaging to provide social proof on the product. Use a combination of <a href="https://classcast.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/203954193">web based surveys and personal communication</a> to continue gathering feedback about how the product is being used and why the chose to purchase or not purchase.\r\n<h2><strong>Summary</strong></h2>\r\nEffective internal and customer communication is a strong driver of product success. Most importantly, continued feedback from customers is used to drive ongoing product innovation, modifications to the marketing messaging or pricing. Beginning your product journey with effective communication as a key goal will ensure you’ve had the time to refine messaging along the way so when the product finally goes to market you are setting yourself up for success.', 'Communication across the lifecycle for product success', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '407-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-09 20:00:51', '2014-10-09 20:00:51', '', 407, 'http://www.classcast.co/407-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
